question:
Q1: What is the time complexity of adding a new node to the front of a LinkedList?
A. O(1)
B. O(n)
C. O(n^2)
D. O(log n)

Q2: What is the time complexity of adding a new node to a specific index of a LinkedList?
A. O(1)
B. O(n)
C. O(n^2)
D. O(log n)

Q3: What is the primary advantage of using an array over an ArrayList?
A. Size doesn't change
B. Slight efficiency boost
C. Primitives
D. Gaps in data
answer:
Q1: A. O(1)
Q2: B. O(n)
Q3: A. Size doesn't change
